{
  "texts": [
    "It is aligned with previous studies that concerns about unethical, dishonest, and irresponsible uses of ChatGPT including cheating and plagiarism, that violate academic integrity are driving the decision to ban ChatGPT [30], Sullivan et al. [46] as well as the inclusion of AI output detectors to detect content generate by AI in editorial process under educational setting [19].",
    "In the previous phase, universities in Hong Kong had not been taking solid action regarding how ChatGPT is advised to be used for teaching and learning in university.",
    "However, the CUHK incident brought out the urgency for universities to respond faster.",
    "Soon, EdUHK also announced their stand in supporting the use of ChatGPT, as well as released a set of pedagogical approaches for faculty staff to adopt GenAI in their courses.",
    "This swift university response was noted in the study of Xiao et al. [56], however, it may also highlight the need for a thorough strategy that carefully weighs the risks and safeguards connected to the implementation of ChatGPT with the newly designed course and assessment methods into academia.Phase three is the adaption period."
  ]
}